title: Doctors, students and activists team up to lead fight against NEET irregularities
FM to meet economists, farm bodies for pre-Budget talk
Congress to review 'problem' states, revamp AICC and state units

description: The Kolkata Police have lodged a zero FIR against Bengal governor C V Ananda Bose's nephew linked to rape and criminal conspiracy allegations levelled against Bose and the nephew by an Odissi dancer, saying she was assaulted in a Delhi hotel in Jan 2023. The case, based on a complaint filed at Kolkata's Hare Street police station in Oct last year, has been transferred to the Delhi Police on orders of the chief metropolitan magistrate's court.
title: Zero FIR against Bengal governor's kin over dancer's rape charge

description: Calcutta high court has mandated Bengal govt to ensure a 1% reservation for transgender persons in all public jobs, noting that no quota was offered to the community despite the existing policy advocating equal treatment in employment. In his ruling on Friday, Justice Rajasekhar Mantha instructed the state's chief secretary to enforce this reservation, referencing the 2014 Supreme Court's NALSA judgment - the first to legally recognise non-binary gender identities and uphold the fundamental rights of transgender people.
title: Ensure 1% job quota for transgenders, HC tells Bengal govt

description: Tamil Nadu CM MK Stalin has reiterated his party DMK's demand to stop NEET, highlighting complaints about alleged irregularities in the medical entrance test this year. In a post on X on Sunday, Stalin cited Gujarat police FIRs pertaining to invigilators allegedly tampering with OMR sheets in exchange for money amid claims about cheques, some of several crores and others blank.
title: MK Stalin reiterates 'stop NEET' demand

description: Punjab and Haryana high court has made it clear that there cannot be any discrimination in granting family pension to legally adopted children merely on account of the date of their adoption. The court was of the view that children adopted post-retirement cannot be deprived of pensionary benefits. Justice Tribhuvan Dahiya passed the order while allowing a petition filed by Vikas Kumar, resident of Haryana's Jhajjar district.
title: Kids adopted after retirement can't be denied pension: HC
Can't set timeframe for speaker to accept MLA resignation: HC
Attempt to implement uniform holy mass in churches triggers protests, clashes in Kerala
Congress: Shifting statues in Parliament breach of 'spirit of democracy'

description: The minister said after not fulfilling the promise of transferring Rs 8,500/month to a woman of each family, Congress-governed Karnataka had saddled people with the burden of paying Rs 3/litre more for petrol and diesel. Minister Puri said with this increase, petrol in Karnataka was now Rs 8.2/litre more expensive than BJP-run govts in Uttar Pradesh and Gujarat.
title: Puri takes dig at Congress for Karnataka fuel price hike

description: Darshan's fan Renuka Swamy started sending the star's girlfriend Pavithra Gowda messages through a fake Instagram profile two weeks before his June 8 murder and the messages turned lewd in the week before his killing allegedly at the hands of the actor and his aides, according to a senior police officer. Police have also claimed that Swamy messaged, some with obscene content, many other women. These including a couple of actresses.
title: Darshan fan's lewd messages to her from fake profile angered Pavithra, led to his killing: Cops

description: A beehive of Pakistani spies posing as young Indian women with alluring names honeytraps officials in Indian defence establishments, reveal court papers about Nishant Agrawal, a former scientist of Brahmos Aerospace Private Limited's (BAPL) Nagpur unit recently convicted of leaking military secrets. Many could fall for the Indian-sounding Sejal Kapoor, Arohi Alok, Aditi Aaron, Aditi Agrawal, Anamika Sharma, Divya Chandan Roy, Neha Sharma and Pooja Ranjan. Agrawal did so, too, six years ago.
title: Pak spies pose as Indian girls to honeytrap desi def officials

description: Indian Railways operated the first trial train from Sangaldan to Reasi, including on the world's highest rail bridge built on Chenab river in J&K, on Sunday. With this rail link, travel between the Valley and the rest of the country is set to become a reality in the next 4-5 months, officials said. Reasi was recently in the news because of a terror attack that claimed nine lives. The railways also achieved this feat days before PM Narendra Modi visits Srinagar to celebrate International Yoga Day.
title: 1st trial train reaches Reasi in J&K via highest rail bridge
Bihar ASI hit by tractor ferrying illegally mined sand, badly hurt

description: India and the US are now in an "advanced stage of talks" for the proposed joint manufacture of the latest generation of Stryker armoured infantry combat vehicles (ICVs) as part of their defence-industrial cooperation roadmap. With the US also recently offering to demonstrate the mobility and firepower of the eight-wheeled Stryker in high-altitude areas in India, the defence ministry is examining a three-phase plan for the proposed project, sources told TOI.
title: India, US in 'advanced stage of talks' for combat vehicles
Man arrested in Rajasthan over video threatening to kill Salman Khan

description: Steps to boost jobs by expanding the Production Linked Incentive scheme to furniture, toys, footwear and more segments of textiles, along with a focus on MSMEs, while increasing income levels of women and boosting infrastructure, are expected to be among the key thrust areas of the Modi govt's first Budget in its third term with several of the issues also being part of govt's 100-day agenda that will feed into the targets for 2030.
title: 1st Modi 3.0 Budget to eye job creation by expanding PLI scheme, MSME focus
Villagers in Maoist dens vow to keep guerrillas out
4 women sharing Noida flat among dead in bus crash
NCERT chief: Riot lessons in texts can create 'violent citizens'

description: Taking a serious view of the row over National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test for admission to medical colleges, education minister Dharmendra Pradhan on Sunday said no one, including officials of National Testing Agency that conducts the exams, would be spared if irregularities were found, and interests of all students who took the test would be protected. Govt is looking at reforms to ensure that such problems do not occur in future.
title: Some irregularities in NEET at specific locations detected: Pradhan

description: Amid growing speculation that BJP leadership may prefer his continuation as Lok Sabha Speaker, Om Birla on Sunday said the decision would be made by all political parties. Changes should keep happening. But I am nobody to comment on this. The Speaker's post will be decided by political parties in the House," he said. Speculation about Birla getting a second term as Speaker has gathered force amid strong indications that the constitutional position will stay with BJP, the single largest party in LoK Sabha by a huge margin and, also, that two of its crucial allies - TDP and JD(U) - are comfortable with the idea.
title: Speaker's post will be decided by parties: Om Birla

description: The Jammu division of J&K - which witnessed back-to-back terror attacks in its Reasi, Kathua and Doda districts last week - is set to get a big boost in number of security forces who will dominate the mountain tops to tackle fresh infiltration bids by terrorists from Pakistan. The security forces will also comb the forested and undulating terrain for terrorists holed up there with an intent to create unrest and communal flare-up among the region's mixed Hindu-Muslim population.
title: After terror strikes, Shah reviews scene; Jammu troop levels to go up

description: With allegations of unauthorised EVM access intensifying, the Mumbai Suburban Returning Officer (RO) issued a rebuttal on Sunday and notices to publications that carried reports on the use of a phone by a polling agent in the Mumbai North-West Lok Sabha constituency. The RO, Vandana Suryavanshi, clarified that EVMs are standalone devices without wired connectivity and need no OTPs on mobile phones for unlocking.
title: Election commission junks report of tampering at Mumbai booth

description: Electronic voting machines (EVMs) were once again in focus with Elon Musk, the multi-billionaire founder of Tesla and SpaceX, and former Union minister Rajeev Chandrasekhar engaging in a debate on X after Musk suggested eliminating the machines following reports of EVM irregularities in Puerto Rico's primary elections. Chandrasekhar, a former MoS for electronics and IT, strongly disagreed with Musk and said it was a "huge sweeping generalisation" that held no truth for the EVMs used in India which are standalone systems not connected to the internet.
title: EVMs can be hacked, says Elon Musk; not in India counters ex-IT minister

description: Authorities on Sunday identified the man who opened fire at a splash pad in suburban Detroit before taking his own life as 42-year-old Michael William Nash of Shelby Township. Oakland County Sheriff Mike Bouchard stated that Nash had no prior criminal history but appeared to be privately struggling with mental health issues. However, no one was aware of his challenges.​
title: Police identify Michigan splash pad shooter, still no word on motive

description: Natalie Dau, a 52-year-old ultramarathoner, recently completed an astonishing feat by running 1,000 kilometres across Thailand, Malaysia, and Singapore in just 12 days. Facing extreme heat and a severe hip injury, Ms Dau pushed through, covering the distance of two marathons each day.  Her journey ended in Singapore on June 5, setting the Singapore record for the "Fastest 1,000km Thailand-Singapore Ultramarathon" and awaiting certification from Guinness World Records for the "Fastest Crossing of Peninsular Malaysia on Foot."
title: Woman ran 1,000 km, says heat melted her shoes
Yemen's Houthis attacks two ships and American destroyer

description: The issue of Russia’s absence loomed large at the peace summit in Switzerland, as India joined over a dozen other countries in not signing a joint communique that declared any peace agreement must be based on Ukraine’s territorial integrity. India backed out saying abiding peace isn’t possible in the absence of options acceptable to both sides, as the summit also could not elicit the kind of support Ukraine was hoping for from the Global South.
title: Russia absent, India refuses to endorse peace communique
Amid search for terrorists, J&K police warn against rumours
Arizona man charged for plotting mass shooting at concert

description: Under-fire Pakistan skipper Babar Azam on Sunday achieved a remarkable feat as he surpassed legendary MS Dhoni in the list of most run-getters as a captain in the history of the T20 World Cup during their match against Ireland in Lauderhill, United States. Leading from the front, these captains have demonstrated remarkable skill and composure under pressure, etching their names into the history of the tournament with substantial run tallies.
title: Babar surpasses Dhoni to achieve this big record as captain in T20 WCs

description: Pakistan skipper Babar Azam guided his team to victory over Ireland on Sunday, with an unbeaten 32, in their final game at the T20 World Cup, avoiding another embarrassing loss for his already eliminated side. Shaheen Shah Afridi took three wickets and then hit two sixes to win the game as Pakistan ended a disappointing tournament with a three-wicket win at Central Broward Stadium.
title: T20 WC: Pakistan bow out with win over Ireland

description: Starting July 2024, Assam government officials, including the Chief Minister and Chief Secretary, will pay their electricity bills, ending the 'VIP culture' of using taxpayer money. All public servants will be responsible for their electricity consumption, aligning with efforts to transition to solar power in medical colleges and universities.
title: This 'VIP culture' to end in Assam from July

description: The grand finale of Bigg Boss Malayalam 6 saw Jinto Bodycraft emerge victorious, winning Rs 50 lakhs amidst intense competition. His journey, marked by resilience and controversy, culminated in a significant achievement. Upon winning the title, Jinto expressed his surprise and gratitude, thanking God, his family, and his co-contestants for their support throughout his journey.
title: Physical trainer Jinto Bodycraft wins Bigg Boss Malayalam 6
Two jawans dead, 7 hurt after bus collides with auto in Maharashtra

description: American citizen Trevor Bokstaahlar's body was found in a ravine between Kee and Tashigang in Himachal Pradesh's Lahaul and Spiti district after he went missing during his visit to Spiti Valley.
title: Missing American citizen's body found in Himachal
Prerna Sthal: Cong slams BJP for moving statues 'unilaterally'

description: Heatwave with temperatures exceeding 46 degrees Celsius continues in Uttar Pradesh, with Prayagraj reaching 47.6 degrees Celsius, the hottest in India. The Met department forecasts no relief for the next two days.

'Will work for the nation together': Rijiju meets Kharge

description: Eid-ul-Adha, the Festival of Sacrifice, symbolizes faith and compassion, honoring Prophet Ibrahim's sacrifice. Muslims worldwide gather for prayers and festive celebrations, exchanging Eid Mubarak wishes to convey love and blessings across communities.

description: Indian railway ministry conducts successful trial of train from Sangaldan to Reasi, including crossing the world's highest steel arch rail bridge Chenab, as part of the USBRL project.
title: Watch: Train engine crosses world's highest steel arch rail bridge
Tactical pause stokes divide in Israel's war cabinet

description: The Jordanian foreign ministry announced that 14 of their pilgrims had died and 17 others were missing during the hajj rituals. The ministry later confirmed that the 14 pilgrims had passed away 'after suffering sun stroke due to the extreme heat wave.' Iranian Red Crescent chief Pirhossein Koolivand reported that 'five Iranian pilgrims have lost their lives so far in Mecca and Medina during the hajj this year,' without specifying the causes of their deaths.

Why India did not sign Ukraine Peace Summit joint statement

description: Former Indian cricketer Navjot Singh Sidhu praised Suryakumar Yadav for his unbeaten half-century against the United States in the ongoing T20 World Cup at the Nassau International Cricket Stadium in New York. Despite a slow start in the first two matches, Suryakumar bounced back with a 50-run knock off 49 balls, which included two fours and two sixes, at a strike rate of 102.04. Sidhu highlighted that a significant portion of Suryakumar's runs against the USA came in the fine-leg area.
title: 'He has made areas where playing shots was considered a crime'

description: NHAI will now invite separate bids from companies interested in developing wayside amenities on national highways. The objective behind this decision is to attract global expertise in creating such amenities.
title: ‘World-class’: NHAI aims for global expertise for amenities on highways

description: In Jhansi village, a tragic bus accident occurred on Sunday morning, injuring 12 pilgrims from Jharkhand and West Bengal on their way to Kedarnath shrine. Three seriously injured pilgrims were referred to Varanasi for treatment. The group of 30 pilgrims had hired the bus for the pilgrimage. The injured were taken to the district hospital for medical care.
title: 12 pilgrims injured as bus rams into truck in Chandauli

description: In today's entertainment news: Aamir Khan and Genelia Deshmukh wrap up filming for 'Sitaare Zameen Par.' Anushka Sharma shares daughter Vamika's footprint art for Father's Day. Mumbai Police arrest a man for threatening Salman Khan. Varun Dhawan shares the first picture of his daughter. 'Pushpa 2,' starring Allu Arjun, now aims for a December release.

description: Amid controversy over EVM security, a poll official clarified that Electronic Voting Machines lack wireless communication and do not require OTPs for operation. Mumbai's North West constituency faced scrutiny after a candidate's aide allegedly misused a mobile phone at a counting center. FIRs were filed, and forensic investigations were initiated. The incident occurred during a closely contested election won by Shiv Sena's Ravindra Waikar.

description: A passenger criticized Air India for a nightmare experience on a Newark-bound flight, citing unclean seats and uncooked food on Twitter. He also claimed the flight was delayed and didn't get a flatbed. His post has got over 149k views. He also said that his luggage was broken by the Air India.
title: 'Stale food, bad seats': Flyer recounts 'nightmare' flight
Use area domination, zero-terror plans in Jammu: Amit Shah

description: In tents in the stifling heat and in bombed-out mosques, Gazans marked Sunday the start of the Muslim holiday of Eid al-Adha, devoid of the usual cheer as the Israel-Hamas war raged on. "This Eid is completely different," she said, with many Gazans forced to spend the holiday without their loved ones killed or displaced during the war.

description: NCERT's director Dinesh Prasad Saklani expressed concerns about teaching riots in school textbooks, emphasizing the need to create positive citizens and avoid fostering violence and depression. He specifically mentioned the changes made regarding chapters on Gujarat riots.

description: Shubman Gill has dismissed rumours of indiscipline following his departure from the T20 World Cup squad. Sharing a collage with Rohit Sharma and his daughter, Gill emphasized learning discipline from Sharma. India’s batting coach, Vikram Rathour, clarified that Gill and Avesh Khan’s exit was pre-planned. India topped Group A and advanced to the Super 8 stage.

description: Sanjay Manjrekar emphasized the importance of Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma delivering in crucial T20 World Cup matches despite lackluster performances in the group stage. While skipper Rohit was in fine form during his fifty against Ireland, he didn't score many runs against Pakistan and the USA in the next two games. Meanwhile, Kohli has failed to reach double digits in all three completed games.

description: A study by marine biologists reveals insights into bioluminescence, with focus on octocorals. These soft-bodied corals possess the ability to produce light through internal chemical reactions. Despite its widespread occurrence, the origins and original function of bioluminescence remains unknown. ​​
title: Over 94 organisms have bioluminescence, scientists don't know why

description: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) fined $194.2 million by US District Court for misappropriating trade secrets from Computer Sciences Corporation (CSC), now merged with DXC Technology Company. TCS to appeal against the court order.

description: The T20 World Cup match between Australia and Scotland saw Australia's record-setting fielding lapses despite their eventual five-wicket win. Hosted at Daren Sammy National Cricket Stadium, the match had Super Eight implications, securing England's advancement. Scotland's competitive 180/5 owed to Brandon McMullen's 60 and Richie Berrington's 42. Australia's six drops set a new T20 record.
title: Australia set dropped catches record in T20 WC vs Scotland

description: Former Australian cricketer Ian Chappell criticizes risky pitches at the USA's Nassau County International Stadium during the ICC T20 World Cup, affecting batting challenges and entertainment value. Chappell explained that the USA's reputation for "dodgy pitches" is not new and may actually be linked to a five-match series in Los Angeles in 1999 between India A and Australia A, which included future greats VVS Laxman and Adam Gilchrist as captains.

description: The UK general elections on July 4 face a cybersecurity threat from state actors like China and Russia, with concerns of misinformation, data leaks, and attacks on individuals, posing risks of internal chaos and public manipulation.

description: Australia equals India and England for most consecutive T20 World Cup victories, winning 7 matches in a row since 2022.

description: A total of 58 child laborers, including 39 boys and 19 girls, have been rescued from a distillery in the Raisen district of Madhya Pradesh. This operation was spearheaded by the National Commission for Protection of Child Rights (NCPCR) in collaboration with the Association of Voluntary Action, also known as Bachpan Bachao Andolan (BBA).
title: 58 child labourers with 'burnt wounds' rescued from MP distillery
Paytm said in talks with Zomato to sell movie ticketing business

description: Pune-headquartered PNG jewellers' shop in United States robbed by 20 masked men in broad daylight. Five arrested. Viral CCTV footage shows armed men breaking in.

description: Adidas, the well-known German sports brand, has launched an investigation into a major bribery allegation involving its employees in China. The probe started after the company received a whistleblower complaint. According to a report by Reuters, citing the Financial Times, senior staff in Adidas' China unit are accused of embezzling "millions of euros."

Whether through a simple message or a beautiful card, expressing your sentiments on this holy occasion brings warmth and joy to those you care about. Eid Mubarak!
title: Happy Eid-ul-Adha 2024: Eid Mubarak images, quotes & wishes

title: 17-year-old preparing for IIT-JEE dies by suicide in Rajasthan's Kota

description: The Israeli army has announced a "tactical pause" in its military operations for humanitarian reasons. This pause will take place from 5:00 GMT to 16:00 GMT, which is 10:30 am to 9:30 am in Indian Standard Time (IST). The pause will be observed along the road from Kerem Shalom crossing to Salah al-Din Road, extending northwards.
title: Israel to give its Gaza action 'tactical pause' for aid purposes
Trump challenges Biden to a cognitive test — Then flubs name!

description: In Pakistan's Charsadda town, the police successfully intervened to prevent the marriage of a 12-year-old girl to a 72-year-old man named Habib Khan. The authorities arrested the groom and the 'Nikah Khwan' (the person who officiates the marriage), although the girl's father managed to escape. A case has been registered against the girl's father, the elderly groom, and the 'Nikah Khwan' under the Child Marriage Act.
title: 12-yr-old in Pak forced to marry 72-yr-old man, cops rescue her

description: Union home minister Amit Shah chaired a high-level meeting in New Delhi to assess the security situation in Jammu and Kashmir with key officials, including NSA Ajit Doval, discussing recent terrorist attacks and preparations for the Amarnath Yatra.
title: Amit Shah holds high-level meet to review J&K security situation

description: A man opened fire at a splash pad in US's Detroit injuring at least 8. Oakland County Sheriff Mike Bouchard informed that among the 8 injured, two are kids with an 8-year-old getting shot in the head. The shooter fired almost 28 times and stopped multiple times to reload. Initial deputies provided immediate medical assistance to the victims.
title: Witnesses recount horror of US waterpark shooting

description: In a pivotal Group B clash in St Lucia, Australia emerged victorious in a closely contested match while chasing 181 to win. The Australians showcased their batting prowess and determination, reaching the target in the final over for a five-wicket win, which eliminated the Scots and booked England a spot in the Super 8s alongside Australia.
title: T20 WC: Aus beat Scots to take Eng along into Super 8s

description: Elon Musk, the multi-billionaire entrepreneur, has suggested that electronic voting machines (EVMs) should be removed due to their vulnerability to hacking by humans or Artificial Intelligence (AI). Musk was reacting to reports of irregularities found in EVMs during Puerto Rico's primary elections. Several media sources noted that there were hundreds of irregularities and multiple glitches in the EVMs.
title: Why Elon Musk thinks we should 'eliminate' electronic voting machines

description: The National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test (NEET) conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA) has stirred controversy in Bahadurgarh. Komal Rani, despite scoring 641 out of 720, faces uncertainty in securing a medical college seat due to grace marks awarded to other candidates. The examination centres at Hardyal Public School and SR Century Public School in Bahadurgarh are under scrutiny for distributing different question paper sets, leading to confusion and time loss for candidates.
title: Haryana's comedy of errors in country's NEET tragedy

description: As the General elections in UK near, opinion polls predict low seat share for the Conservatives. Cautioning Sunak's party of 'electoral extinction', Savanta research forecasts 21% support for the Conservatives, a drop by 4 points.
title: Polls predict 'electoral extinction' for PM Sunak's party in UK

description: In Rajkot, as Chief Minister Bhupendra Patel consoled the families of 27 individuals who died in the TRP Game Zone fire, Rajkot Municipal Corporation officers were arrested for creating fake backdated letters and destroying old registers. Two more officers, Rajesh Makwana and Jaydeep Chaudhary, were arrested, bringing the total to 12. They were involved in creating fake files and tampering with records related to the game zone operators' regularization application.
title: Rajkot game zone fire: Day after 27 deaths, RMC officials tried to destroy evidence

With him, you can be yourself-confident and completely vulnerable-knowing he won't judge you. He is someone you can always confide in and the person you instinctively turn to with your hopes, fears, and dreams, knowing that his advice will be both wise and compassionate.

Navjot Singh Sidhu highlighted inadequate facilities and the need for matches to be decided by skill, not weather. Pakistan's hopes were dashed by rain, affecting key games against the USA and Ireland in Lauderhill.

Authorities have described the incident as a "random" act of gun violence.
